title: ICE: Wrong DefKind in object_lifetime_default

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code I ran `x test src/test/ui-fulldeps/session-diagnostic` in the rust repo. According to cargo this happened while compiling `rustc_graphviz`. I don't have a minimal example or anything and it went away after a `x clean` so it's probably related to incremental. ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: I'm not entirely sure, either the current stage0, 2022-09-20-beta or the current master (2022-10-22) ### Error output ``` thread 'rustc' panicked at 'assertion failed: `(left == right)` left: `Enum`, right: `TyParam`', compiler/rustc_hir_analysis/src/collect/lifetimes.rs:1146:5 ``` Full backtrace: https://pastebin.com/VtWYFQxF
